vulnerabilities.suggested_fix:
Restrict `newOwner` so only an existing authorized account can add owners, e.g.:
- Add `onlyOwner` (or `require(msg.sender == root)`) to `newOwner`.
Example:
```solidity
function newOwner(address _owner) external onlyOwner returns (bool) {
    require(_owner != address(0));
    require(owners[_owner] == address(0));
    owners[_owner] = msg.sender;
    return true;
}
```
Additionally consider explicit role management (e.g., OpenZeppelin AccessControl/Ownable) and events for owner changes.
